Greetings Kindergarten Families!

We value the speech and language development of your young learners! Therefore, we provide a speech/language screener to every incoming Kindergarten student so that we know how to best support their skills. Our SLP (speech/language teacher), Lindsey Massenzio would like to meet with you and your child on zoom to complete the screener.

If you are already signed up for a speech/language screener zoom session with our SLP, Lindsey Massenzio, here is the zoom information:
https://us04web.zoom.us/j/77894043727?pwd=STVseVdOVHdQakxSLzdWSVpNRXl2QT09

Meeting ID: 778 9404 3727
Passcode: Dragons

If you have not yet signed up for a speech/language screener session, please reach out to your child‚Äôs classroom teacher to schedule a time.

Thank you!

post_text:
Incoming Kindergarteners:
We will be unable to do our in-person Dragon Training the first week of September. Your child's teacher will be in contact next week with details about what school will look like and to set up a time to have a family meeting. We are excited to meet your kindergartner on September 9th virtually. This is something you and your children will be talking about someday as the first kindergarten class to start school virtually during a global pandemic.
You are all now part of our crew and we are in this together. We promise to make this the best possible kindergarten experience for your family!

Wishing there was a drive in movie located a little closer to home? No problem! The Greece Town Board is pleased to invite Greece residents to join us for our first ever ‚ÄúDrive-In Family Movie Night‚Äù premiering at the Greece Town Hall Campus.

Pre-registration is required for the screening of Disney Pixar ONWARD. To ensure social distancing, we will be limiting this event to 85 cars. The price will be $5 per car, which includes a bag of popcorn to enjoy. Please also feel free to bring your own snacks and a lawn chair as well and join your neighbors for an evening of fun under the stars!

Registration will begin Friday, May 29th at 8:00 AM. Those interested may register on-line by accessing our Rec-Trac system on the Greece Parks and Recreation website https://greeceparksandrec.greeceny.gov/wbwsc/webtrac.wsc/splash.html?InterfaceParameter=WebTrac_1

post_text:
We have modified our daily share to ensure all of our student and families can participate. Many our families are celebrating Eid which does not allow all to participate in our food shares.

Eid literally means a "festival" or "feast" in Arabic. Eid al-Fitr, as it follows the fasting of Ramadan, is also seen as a spiritual celebration of Allah's provision of strength and endurance. Eid is meant to be a time of joy and blessing for the entire Muslim community and a time for distributing one's wealth.

Eid Mubarak!

City of Rochester, NY - Mayor's Office
May 16 at 6:45 PM ¬∑

Beginning Monday, May 18, the Central Library of Rochester and Monroe County will begin offering more MiFi mobile hotspot units and contactless curbside pickup of library materials. These services are available for any library cardholder who needs internet access at home or would like to borrow physical library materials, such as books and DVDs.

Call 428-7300 to request materials for pickup. Library staff will locate the desired items and schedule a pick-up date and time that will take place between the hours of 9:30 a.m. ‚Äì 2 p.m.

Patrons are asked to arrive promptly at their scheduled appointment time to help maintain proper social distancing.

City of Rochester, NY - Mayor's Office
May 5 at 3:54 PM ¬∑

Good news for NW Rochester children and families! Beginning tomorrow (Wednesday, May 6) play kits will also be available for distribution at School No. 7, 31 Bryan St. Play kits will be available on a first-come, first-served basis during normal meal distribution hours, which are 8 a.m. - 2:30 p.m. at RCSD sites.

Play kits are also available (while supplies last) from 8 a.m.- 5:30 p.m. at the nine City R-Center meal distribution sites.

The Department of Recreation & Youth Services and Healthi Kids plan to partner again in the next few weeks to distribute a second round of play kits at R-Center and RCSD meal distribution sites throughout the city. Stay tuned....we'll let you know when that's going to happen.
